claude/agents/ai-council.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/deep-research.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/context.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/review.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/debug.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/code.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/prompt-improver.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/markdown.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/orchestrate.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/agents/README.txt\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":12,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780130098609,\"end\":1780130098692}},\"id\":\"prt_e7805ad75001zAt0aY8yGcqUkG\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e780584a6001i0yOj9R1eD0cit\"}}\n\n  Line 27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780130098733,\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_function_ptyqpfa4xd4i_5\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".gemini/agents/**/*\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/deep-review.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/ai-council.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/deep-research.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/context.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/prompt-improver.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/markdown.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/orchestrate.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/README.txt\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/code.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/debug.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.gemini/agents/review.md\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":12,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780130098662,\"end\":1780130098732}},\"id\":\"prt_e7805adb4001vSY7ldwMouYiNB\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e780584a6001i0yOj9R1eD0cit\"}}\n\n  Line 34: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780130147136,\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_function_4o3egtrbae1u_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Iteration 5 (MiniMax-M2.7): RQ6 — Rename Surface + Safe Ordering\\n\\n## Focus\\n\\nRQ6: exhaustive rename surface map + SAFE ORDERING for `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement`, covering all surfaces, dangling-reference risks, and phase-gating constraints that determine whether Lane C should be built before or after the rename.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Actions Taken\\n\\n1. **Re-read** the live skill-advisor TypeScript scorer files — `aliases.ts` and `lanes/explicit.ts` — to confirm the exact alias group shape and phrase-boost matrix that Phase 002 must update. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:27-48] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:98-139]\\n\\n2. **Re-read** the Python skill-advisor shim for the same alias surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:250] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:1576]\\n\\n3. **Glob-surveyed** all four runtime mirror trees (`.opencode/agents/`, `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`) to inventory the agent mirror surfaces that Phase 002 must handle simultaneously. [SOURCE: glob results — .opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .claude/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml, .gemini/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md]\\n\\n4. **Read** the `deep-agent-improvement` SKILL.md frontmatter and §10 INTEGRATION POINTS for the exact `description` field text and skill-advisor `enhances` edge surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:1-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:520-525]\\n\\n5. **Read** the sibling packet 121 context-index for the Phase 002 rena...\n  Line 40: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780130162589,\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_function_d5w23t0iywi3_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5,\\\"model\\\":\\\"minimax\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.6,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"iter5\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-01\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Alias Groups: six hard-coded strings (aliases.ts:27-32, explicit.ts:116-119) plus Python shim (skill_advisor.py:250,1576) must be updated in paired Phase 002 step\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-02\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Phrase-boost matrix has both positive (1.5-1.6) and negative (-0.4 to -0.6) entries for old name; negative penalties become inert post-rename and impair benchmark disambiguation\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-03\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Four runtime mirror trees (.opencode, .claude, .codex, .gemini) all have deep-agent-improvement named agent; must be renamed together as one step\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-04\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"CLI command files body text and .codex/config.toml registration name the old skill; must update alongside mirror rename\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-05\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"deep-model-benchmark alias group may also need rename decision; must be explicitly decided in Phase 002 decision-record\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-06\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"description.json auto-regeneration requires explicit generate-context.js invocation post-git-mv; not automatic\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-07\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"sk-prompt-models SKILL.md cross-references deep-agent-improvement; must update during Phase 002\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":5}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-minimax-i5-08\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"HARD GATE: Lane C trace-normalization root changes with skill dir rename; building Lane...\n  Line 43: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1780130189900,\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e7806bc3b001SzRp6qn5jISkV3\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e7806a9f2001SrcW8HPQ301DSI\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_187fad801ffeWPEGDcOeyHwZyu\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n# Iteration 5 (MiniMax-M2.7): RQ6 — Rename Surface + Safe Ordering\\n\\n## Focus\\n\\nRQ6: exhaustive rename surface map + SAFE ORDERING for `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement`, covering all surfaces, dangling-reference risks, and phase-gating constraints that determine whether Lane C should be built before or after the rename.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Actions Taken\\n\\n1. **Re-read** the live skill-advisor TypeScript scorer files — `aliases.ts` and `lanes/explicit.ts` — to confirm the exact alias group shape and phrase-boost matrix that Phase 002 must update. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:27-48] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:98-139]\\n\\n2. **Re-read** the Python skill-advisor shim for the same alias surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:250] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:1576]\\n\\n3. **Glob-surveyed** all four runtime mirror trees (`.opencode/agents/`, `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`) to inventory the agent mirror surfaces that Phase 002 must handle simultaneously. [SOURCE: glob results — .opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .claude/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml, .gemini/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md]\\n\\n4. **Read** the `deep-agent-improvement` SKILL.md frontmatter and §10 INTEGRATION POINTS for the exact `description` field text and skill-advisor `enhances` edge surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:1-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:520-525]\\n\\n5. **Read** the sibling packet 121 conte...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/deltas/iter-005.jsonl:\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-minimax-i5-03\",\"label\":\"Four runtime mirror trees (.opencode, .claude, .codex, .gemini) all have deep-agent-improvement named agent; must be renamed together as one step\",\"iteration\":5}\n\n  Line 8: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-minimax-i5-07\",\"label\":\"sk-prompt-models SKILL.md cross-references deep-agent-improvement; must update during Phase 002\",\"iteration\":5}\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/iterations/iteration-005.md:\n  Line 5: RQ6: exhaustive rename surface map + SAFE ORDERING for `deep-agent-improvement` → `deep-improvement`, covering all surfaces, dangling-reference risks, and phase-gating constraints that determine whether Lane C should be built before or after the rename.\n\n  Line 15: 3. **Glob-surveyed** all four runtime mirror trees (`.opencode/agents/`, `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`) to inventory the agent mirror surfaces that Phase 002 must handle simultaneously. [SOURCE: glob results — .opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .claude/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md, .codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml, .gemini/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md]\n\n  Line 17: 4. **Read** the `deep-agent-improvement` SKILL.md frontmatter and §10 INTEGRATION POINTS for the exact `description` field text and skill-advisor `enhances` edge surface. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:1-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:520-525]\n\n  Line 19: 5. **Read** the sibling packet 121 context-index for the Phase 002 rename scope and success criteria definition. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:36] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:37-50]\n\n  Line 23: 7. **Read** the `sk-prompt-models` SKILL.md for the `deep-agent-improvement` sentinel reference. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md:202-229]\n\n  Line 31: The skill-advisor TypeScript scorer hard-codes `deep-agent-improvement` as a canonical alias-group key and as a phrase-boost target in `aliases.ts:27-32` and `explicit.ts:116-119`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:116] The group contains four aliases: `command-spec-kit-deep-agent-improvement`, `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, `deep-agent-improvement`, `sk-deep-agent-improvement`. All four must be renamed to `deep-improvement`-equivalent forms, and the existing `deep-model-benchmark` alias group must also be assessed — if `deep-agent-improvement` is renamed, the benchmark lane alias group may need renaming too (e.g., to `deep-model-benchmark` → `deep-benchmark` or similar), but that decision is Phase 002 policy.\n\n  Line 39: The `explicit.ts` phrase-boost matrix includes both positive boosts for `deep-agent-improvement`-related phrases and negative penalties targeting the old id when benchmark phrasing appears. Specifically:\n\n  Line 40: - `'5d scoring'` → `[['deep-agent-improvement', 1.5]]`\n\n  Line 41: - `'5-dimension agent scoring'` → `[['deep-agent-improvement', 1.6]]`\n\n  Line 42: - `'integration scan'` → `[['deep-agent-improvement', 1.5]]`\n\n  Line 43: - `'dynamic profile'` → `[['deep-agent-improvement', 1.5]]`\n\n  Line 44: - `'benchmark a model'` → `[['deep-model-benchmark', 1.6], ['deep-agent-improvement', -0.6]]`\n\n  Line 46: The negative entries mean that during the transition window, a prompt containing benchmark phrasing would receive a negative penalty against `deep-agent-improvement`. If Phase 002 updates the positive targets but leaves the negative penalty strings unchanged, the penalty would still hit the old id (now a non-existent skill), which is inert but also means the disambiguation logic for benchmark vs. agent-improvement is temporarily impaired. This is not a breaking failure but a degraded state.\n\n  Line 48: **Actionable**: Phase 002 should update the positive boost targets to `deep-improvement` AND update or remove the negative penalties referencing `deep-agent-improvement`, replacing them with equivalent penalties against the new id if the disambiguation semantics are to be preserved.\n\n  Line 50: ### F-MINIMAX-I5-03: Four Runtime Mirror Trees — Each Has a `deep-agent-improvement` Named Surface\n\n  Line 52: All four agent mirror directories contain a file named `deep-agent-improvement` (`.md` for three runtimes, `.toml` for Codex):\n\n  Line 53: - `.opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md`\n\n  Line 54: - `.claude/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md`\n\n  Line 55: - `.codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml`\n\n  Line 56: - `.gemini/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md`\n\n  Line 58: The skill-advisor `graph-metadata.json` `enhances` edge for `deep-agent-improvement` currently reads:\n\n  Line 60: {\"target\": \"deep-agent-improvement\", \"weight\": 0.7, \"context\": \"routes agent improvement requests\", \"auto_added_at\": \"2026-05-15T14:10:44.259Z\", \"auto_added_reason\": \"family-inference:0.45 + asset-shape:0.30 + sibling-transitivity:0.15\"}\n\n  Line 64: The Phase 002 success criteria require \"zero dangling operational old-name references where the new name is intended, plus advisor rebuild/validate.\" The four mirror files are the most visible operational surfaces — if an operator invokes `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` after the rename and the agent mirror still responds as `deep-agent-improvement`, the experience is broken even if all internal routing is correct.\n\n  Line 70: The two deep-loop command files (`start-agent-improvement-loop.md` and `start-model-benchmark-loop.md`) both contain body text that names `deep-agent-improvement` as the orchestration target. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md:17] These are documentation files, not executable code, but they are user-facing and would show stale references if Phase 002 does not update them.\n\n  Line 72: Additionally, the `.codex/config.toml` registers the agent mirror under the old id. [SOURCE: confirmed by glob — `.codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml` exists and is the only agent mirror for Codex]\n\n  Line 88: ### F-MINIMAX-I5-07: Sentinel Skill `sk-prompt-models` References `deep-agent-improvement` in Its Cross-Reference Table\n\n  Line 90: The `sk-prompt-models` SKILL.md §5 REFERENCES lists `deep-agent-improvement` as a routing/agent target in the skill boundary map at lines 202-213. Specifically, it references `../cli-devin/references/quota-fallback.md` — which is unrelated — but the broader integration table in `SKILL.md:70-78` of `sk-prompt-models` mentions deep-agent-improvement as an agent/command target. The Phase 002 success criteria require \"zero dangling operational old-name references where the new name is intended,\" so this reference must be updated.\n\n  Line 96: Prior iterations (iteration-004 MiniMax) established that building Lane C against `deep-agent-improvement` and then renaming to `deep-improvement` would require rebuilding all trace normalization roots. [SOURCE: iteration-004.md:260] This is because Lane C's benchmark harness resolves the skill root dynamically to find `INTENT_SIGNALS`, `RESOURCE_MAP`, and `RUNTIME_ASSETS`. If the harness is built against the old path and the directory is renamed, every hard-coded path constant in the harness breaks.\n\n  Line 100: - **Option B (Rename After)**: Build Lane C against `deep-agent-improvement` with explicit path constants that will be updated post-rename. Requires Phase 002 to do a full Lane C path update in addition to all other rename surfaces.\n\n  Line 108: The Phase 002 spec calls for running `rg 'deep-agent-improvement'` and classifying every hit as active operational, active documentation, generated/cache, or historical/archive. This step is the gate that ensures no surface is missed. The prior iterations' grep surveys confirm there are 80+ files across the repo containing this string, spanning skill internals, advisor metadata, runtime mirrors, command files, and cross-skill references. [SOURCE: iteration-003-deepseek:27]\n\n  Line 116: The skill-advisor has two implementations: the TypeScript MCP server (`aliases.ts`, `explicit.ts`) and the Python fallback shim (`skill_advisor.py`). Both carry the `deep-agent-improvement` alias group and phrase-boost matrix. During the rename, updating only the TypeScript files would leave the Python shim with stale references, causing a split-brain failure if the runtime ever falls back to the Python path (e.g., when the MCP daemon is unavailable).\n\n  Line 128: 2. **Produce the four-column freeze inventory before any rename step.** File | Classification | Action | Verification for every `deep-agent-improvement` hit across `.opencode/`, `.codex/`, `.claude/`, `.gemini/`, and the Python shim. This prevents dangling references and is the gate for Phase 002 success criteria. [F-MINIMAX-I5-09]\n\n  Line 134: 5. **Update or remove the negative phrase-penalties referencing `deep-agent-improvement`.** The benchmark-vs-agent-improvement disambiguation penalties in `explicit.ts:130-138` currently target `deep-agent-improvement`. After rename, these are inert. Phase 002 should either remove them or map them to the new id if the disambiguation semantics are to be preserved. [F-MINIMAX-I5-02]\n\n  Line 140: 8. **Update `sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md` cross-references** to point to `deep-improvement` instead of `deep-agent-improvement`. [F-MINIMAX-I5-07]\n\n  Line 150: **OQ-MINIMAX-I5-01**: Should the post-rename advisor keep backward-compatible aliases for `deep-agent-improvement` so that old command strings and skill mentions continue to work during a transition window? This would ease migration but would leave the old name as an active operational reference, conflicting with the \"zero dangling old-name references\" success criterion. The alternative is a hard cutover where old names produce explicit errors with migration guidance.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public