{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780130237934,"sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_33a2h0eYYFOS9f2y4sf93609","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 002: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\n3: description: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 002\"\n7:   - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Authored phase scaffold spec (planned)\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Execute rename after Phase 001 impact map converges\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 0\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 002 — Rename deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Implementation (rename / refactor)\n29: **Status:** Planned (depends on Phase 001 rename impact map)\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Rename the skill `deep-agent-improvement` to `deep-improvement` across every surface so the name reflects its real scope (agents + models + skills). The `-agent-` infix is now misleading.\n36: \n37: ## 2. Scope (surface list — confirmed/expanded by Phase 001 RQ6)\n38: \n39: - `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` → `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/` (dir + `SKILL.md` `name:`/frontmatter/triggers/keywords).\n40: - Commands referencing the skill path: `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` (and the new `/deep:start-skill-benchmark-loop`) — update skill-path references. **Command verbs are NOT renamed** unless Phase 001 shows a reason; the agent-improvement command still improves agents.\n41: - Agent file `.opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md` + runtime mirrors `.claude/agents/`, `.codex/agents/`, `.gemini/agents/`.\n42: - Skill-advisor graph (`system-skill-advisor/.../skill-graph.json`), `descriptions.json`, advisor metadata; run advisor rebuild.\n43: - Cross-references: sentinel `sk-prompt-models`, root `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` agent-routing entries, any other skills/docs that name `deep-agent-improvement`.\n44: - Internal self-references inside the skill's own references/scripts/README.\n45: \n46: ## 3. Approach\n47: \n48: Use `git mv` for the directory to preserve history; then a tracked find-and-replace across the confirmed surface list; then advisor rebuild + validate. Agent-name decision (`@deep-agent-improvement` → `@deep-improvement`?) recorded explicitly in this phase's `decision-record.md`.\n49: \n50: ## 4. Success criteria\n51: \n52: - Zero dangling `deep-agent-improvement` references where `deep-improvement` is intended (grep-clean, allowing intentional historical mentions in archives).\n53: - Skill-advisor rebuild + `advisor_validate` green; skill resolvable under the new name.\n54: - Lane A (`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`) and Lane B (`/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`) still run.\n55: - `validate.sh --strict` green for this phase.\n56: \n57: ## 5. Out of scope\n58: \n59: Lane C build (Phase 003); doc/README three-lane rewrite beyond what the rename requires (Phase 004).\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 002: Rename deep-agent-improvement to deep-improvement\"\ndescription: \"Rename the deep-agent-improvement skill to deep-improvement across skill dir, SKILL.md, commands, agent + runtime mirrors, advisor graph, descriptions.json, and cross-references; zero dangling refs; green advisor rebuild.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-improvement rename\"\n  - \"122 phase 002\"\n  - \"rename deep-agent-improvement\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored phase scaffold spec (planned)\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Execute rename after Phase 001 impact map converges\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 0\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md","time":{"start":1780130237926,"end":1780130237932}},"id":"prt_e7807caf9001TBufREefKgDLY5","sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","messageID":"msg_e7807b201001CLinaHE7kb9M37"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780130238581,"sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_kzFLRQFV94ESoRpUPyaP1780","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: \"Evaluate and improve any agent: 5 dimensions, proposals, scoring, guarded promotion. :auto/:confirm.\"\n3: argument-hint: \"<agent_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--iterations=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n12: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n13: > 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\n14: > 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n15: > 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\n16: >\n17: > This command is **general-agent based** — orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill invocation.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: # 🚨 PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n22: \n23: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n24: \n25: ```\n26: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n27: \n28: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n29: │\n30: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n31: │   ├─ You can orchestrate deep-agent-improvement invocation\n32: │   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n33: │   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n34: │\n35: ├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n36: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to Setup Phase\n37: │\n38: └─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n39:     │\n40:     ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n41:     │\n42:     ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n43:     │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44:     │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n45:     │   │                                                            │\n46:     │   │ This command orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill     │\n47:     │   │ invocation and runs general-agent based.                   │\n48:     │   │                                                            │\n49:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n50:     │   │   /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop [arguments]           │\n51:     │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52:     │\n53:     └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n54: ```\n55: \n56: **Phase Output:**\n57: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: # 🔒 UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n62: \n63: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n64: \n65: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n66: \n67: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n68: \n69: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n70: \n71: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n72: \n73: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_folder}/improvement/agent-improvement-config.json` (shape: `targetPath`, `targetProfile`, `specFolder`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `scoringMode`, `maxIterations`, `agentName`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n74: \n75: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed; `target_path` absence is missing input, not ambiguity, and goes to Tier 3.\n76: \n77: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n78: \n79: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n80: \n81: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n82: \n83: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n84: \n85: ```yaml\n86: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n87:   lane: agent-improvement  # optional; one of: agent-improvement | model-benchmark; defaults to agent-improvement when an agent path is present\n88:   target_path: .opencode/agents/debug.md  # required path matching .opencode/agents/*.md\n89:   target_profile: dynamic  # optional; one of: handover | context-prime | dynamic; derived from target_path when omitted\n90:   spec_folder: specs/041/008  # required spec folder path or explicit runtime folder\n91:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n92:   scoring_mode: dynamic  # dynamic is the current supported scoring mode\n93:   max_iterations: 5  # positive integer\n94: ```\n95: \n96: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over $ARGUMENTS flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n97: \n98: ### Default Resolution Table\n99: \n100: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n101: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n102: | `lane` | Y | explicit flag `--lane` or marker `lane` resolved FIRST (an explicit `--lane=model-benchmark` that conflicts with a supplied agent path fails fast or asks one disambiguation, never silently picks Lane A). Then agent-path presence -> `agent-improvement`. Then benchmark-profile or `--profile` arg -> `model-benchmark` | `agent-improvement` when an agent path is present and no explicit lane | N |\n103: | `target_path` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` agent path, or marker `target_path` | none | N |\n104: | `target_profile` | Y | marker `target_profile`, or auto-detect from `target_path` (`handover` -> `handover`, `context-prime` -> `context-prime`, otherwise `dynamic`) | inferred from `target_path` | N |\n105: | `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, or requires-ask | none | Y |\n106: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n107: | `scoring_mode` | Y | marker `scoring_mode`, Q3 equivalent, or default | `dynamic` | N |\n108: | `max_iterations` | Y | flag `--iterations`, marker `max_iterations`, or default | `5` | N |\n109: \n110: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n111: \n112: **🚨 SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION**\n113: \n114: This workflow uses a SINGLE consolidated prompt to gather ALL required inputs in ONE user interaction.\n115: \n116: **Round-trip optimization:** This workflow requires only 1 user interaction for setup.\n117: \n118: ```\n119: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n120: \n121: 1. CHECK for mode suffix in $ARGUMENTS or command invocation:\n122:    ├─ \":auto\" suffix detected → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (pre-set, omit Q2)\n123:    ├─ \":confirm\" suffix detected → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (pre-set, omit Q2)\n124:    └─ No suffix → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2 in prompt)\n125: \n126: 1B. RESOLVE lane BEFORE the agent-path check (additive; default is Lane A).\n127:    Evaluate EXPLICIT lane signals (--lane flag or marker lane) FIRST, before any\n128:    agent-path inference, so an explicit lane is never shadowed (F-P1-8):\n129:    ├─ IF explicit --lane=model-benchmark OR marker lane=model-benchmark\n130:    │     ├─ AND an agent path (.opencode/agents/*.md) is ALSO present → CONFLICT:\n131:    │     │     do NOT silently pick a lane. Fail fast with a one-line conflict error,\n132:    │     │     or ask ONE disambiguation question (\"Explicit --lane=model-benchmark\n133:    │     │     conflicts with the supplied agent path. Which lane?\"). Resolve before proceeding.\n134:    │     └─ ELSE → lane = \"model-benchmark\" → AUTO-ROUTE (see Lane B routing below).\n135:    ├─ IF explicit --lane=agent-improvement OR marker lane=agent-improvement\n136:    │     → lane = \"agent-improvement\", omit Q(lane), proceed exactly as today (Lane A).\n137:    ├─ IF NO explicit lane AND $ARGUMENTS contains an agent path (.opencode/agents/*.md)\n138:    │     → lane = \"agent-improvement\" (CMD-1: agent path with no explicit lane still\n139:    │       auto-resolves to Lane A unchanged), omit Q(lane), proceed as today.\n140:    ├─ IF NO explicit lane AND a --profile arg / benchmark-profile is present (no agent path)\n141:    │     → lane = \"model-benchmark\" → AUTO-ROUTE (see Lane B routing below).\n142:    └─ IF neither lane signal nor an agent path present AND interactive (no :auto)\n143:          → include Q(lane) as the FIRST question in the consolidated prompt and resolve it before Q0.\n144: \n145:    Lane B routing: AUTO-ROUTE to the dedicated model-benchmark workflow:\n146:    load .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_{auto,confirm}.yaml\n147:    (see /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop). Subsequent questions become the Lane B set\n148:    (profile, outputs/spec_folder, exec, scoring_method, grader, executor+model).\n149:    DO NOT ask Q0/Q1/Q3 (the agent-improvement questions).\n150: \n151: 2. CHECK if $ARGUMENTS contains an agent path (Lane A only; skipped when lane=model-benchmark):\n152:    ├─ IF present (.opencode/agents/*.md) → target_path = detected value, omit Q0\n153:    └─ IF missing → include Q0 in prompt\n154: \n155: 3. CHECK for --spec-folder flag:\n156:    ├─ IF present → spec_folder = value, omit Q1\n157:    └─ IF missing → include Q1 in prompt\n158: \n159: 4. CHECK for --iterations flag:\n160:    ├─ IF present → max_iterations = value\n161:    └─ IF missing → max_iterations = 5 (default)\n162: \n163: 5. List available agents for Q0:\n164:    $ ls .opencode/agents/*.md\n165: \n166: 6. List recent spec folders for Q1:\n167:    $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n168: \n169: 7. ASK user with SINGLE consolidated prompt (include only applicable questions):\n170: \n171:    ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n172:    │ **Before proceeding, please answer:**                          │\n173:    │                                                                │\n174:    │ **Q(lane). Use Case** (only when lane is ambiguous: no agent   │\n175:    │    path and no --lane flag):                                    │\n176:    │    A) Improve an agent file (Lane A)                            │\n177:    │    B) Benchmark a model / prompt framework (Lane B)            │\n178:    │    (If A or an agent path was given, continue with Q0-Q3 below.│\n179:    │     If B, this command auto-routes to                          │\n180:    │     /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop and asks the Lane B set.) │\n181:    │                                                                │\n182:    │ **Q0. Target Agent** (if not provided in command):             │\n183:    │    Which agent would you like to evaluate and improve?         │\n184:    │    [list agents found above]                                   │\n185:    │                                                                │\n186:    │ **Q1. Spec Folder** (if no --spec-folder flag):                 │\n187:    │    A) Use existing spec folder: [list if found]                │\n188:    │    B) Create new spec folder                                   │\n189:    │    C) Use temporary directory                                  │\n190:    │                                                                │\n191:    │ **Q2. Execution Mode** (if no :auto/:confirm suffix):            │\n192:    │    A) Autonomous — run loop without approval gates             │\n193:    │    B) Interactive — confirm at each iteration                   │\n194:    │                                                                │\n195:    │ **Q3. Scoring Mode**:                                          │\n196:    │    A) Dynamic — 5-dimension integration-aware (current release)│\n197:    │                                                                │\n198:    │ Reply format: \"handover, A, A, A\" or                           │\n199:    │ \".opencode/agents/debug.md, B, B, A\"                           │\n200:    └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n201: \n202: 8. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n203: \n204: 9. Parse response and store ALL results:\n205:    - lane = [agent-improvement (Lane A) or model-benchmark (Lane B), resolved in step 1B / Q(lane)]\n206:    - IF lane = model-benchmark → STOP this Lane A parse and HAND OFF to\n207:      /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop using\n208:      .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_{auto,confirm}.yaml;\n209:      the Lane B set (profile, outputs/spec_folder, exec, scoring_method, grader, executor+model)\n210:      replaces the fields below.\n211:    - target_path = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n212:    - target_profile = [derived dynamic profile for the selected target]\n213:    - spec_folder = [from Q1 or --spec-folder]\n214:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n215:    - scoring_mode = [dynamic from Q3]\n216:    - max_iterations = [from --iterations or default 5]\n217: \n218: 10. SET STATUS: ✅ PASSED\n219: \n220: **STOP HERE** - Wait for user to answer ALL applicable questions before continuing.\n221: \n222: ⛔ HARD STOP: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n223: ⛔ NEVER infer target agent from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n224: ⛔ NEVER auto-select spec folder without user confirmation\n225: ⛔ NEVER split these questions into multiple prompts\n226: ⛔ NEVER assume what the user wants based on open files or recent activity\n227: ```\n228: \n229: **Phase Output:**\n230: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n231: - `lane = ________________`\n232: - `target_path = ________________`\n233: - `target_profile = ________________`\n234: - `spec_folder = ________________`\n235: - `execution_mode = ________________`\n236: - `scoring_mode = ________________`\n237: - `max_iterations = ________________`\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## PHASE STATUS VERIFICATION (BLOCKING)\n242: \n243: **Before continuing to the workflow, verify ALL values are set:**\n244: \n245: | FIELD                  | REQUIRED      | YOUR VALUE | SOURCE                  |\n246: | ---------------------- | ------------- | ---------- | ----------------------- |\n247: | general_agent_verified | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Automatic check         |\n248: | lane                   | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Step 1B / Q(lane)       |\n249: | target_path            | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q0 or $ARGUMENTS        |\n250: | target_profile         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Derived from target rules |\n251: | spec_folder            | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q1 or --spec-folder     |\n252: | execution_mode         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Suffix or Q2            |\n253: | scoring_mode           | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q3                      |\n254: | max_iterations         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | --iterations or 5       |\n255: \n256: ```\n257: VERIFICATION CHECK:\n258: ├─ ALL required fields have values?\n259: │   ├─ YES → Proceed to \"INSTRUCTIONS\" section below\n260: │   └─ NO  → Re-prompt for missing values only\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ## CONSTRAINTS\n266: \n267: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n268: - **DO NOT** infer target agent from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n269: - **DO NOT** start the loop without all setup values resolved\n270: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: run Phase 0, run Setup, then load YAML workflow\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: # Improve Agent\n275: \n276: Evaluate and improve any agent across 5 integration-aware dimensions. The skill scans all surfaces the agent touches, derives a scoring profile from the agent's own rules, writes packet-local candidates, scores them deterministically, and only allows promotion when evidence and approval gates are satisfied.\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## 1. PURPOSE\n281: \n282: Run a bounded evaluator-first loop that:\n283: 1. Scans the target agent's full integration surface (mirrors, commands, YAML workflows, skills)\n284: 2. Generates a dynamic scoring profile from the agent's own ALWAYS/NEVER/ESCALATE IF rules\n285: 3. Proposes packet-local candidates without mutating the canonical target\n286: 4. Scores candidates across 5 weighted dimensions (structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, systemFitness)\n287: 5. Runs fixture benchmarks against target-specific test sets\n288: 6. Reduces evidence into a dimensional dashboard with convergence detection (per SKILL canonical stopReason enum: converged | maxIterationsReached | blockedStop | manualStop | error | stuckRecovery)\n289: 7. Stops on canonical stopReason: `converged`, `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `manualStop`, `error`, or `stuckRecovery`\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ## 2. CONTRACT\n294: \n295: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` — agent path, optional mode suffix, optional spec folder, optional iteration count\n296: **Outputs:** improvement packet state under `{spec_folder}/improvement/` + `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n297: \n298: ### User Input\n299: \n300: ```text\n301: $ARGUMENTS\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## 3. 5-DIMENSION REFERENCE\n307: \n308: | Dimension | Weight | What It Measures |\n309: | --- | --- | --- |\n310: | Structural Integrity | 0.20 | Agent template compliance (required sections) |\n311: | Rule Coherence | 0.25 | ALWAYS/NEVER rules align with workflow steps |\n312: | Integration Consistency | 0.25 | Mirrors in sync, commands reference agent, skills reference agent |\n313: | Output Quality | 0.15 | Output verification items present, no placeholder content |\n314: | System Fitness | 0.15 | Permission-capability alignment, resource references valid |\n315: \n316: ### Scoring Modes\n317: \n318: | Mode | Flag | Profiles | Use When |\n319: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n320: | Dynamic | `--dynamic` | Any agent (generated on-the-fly) | Evaluating arbitrary agents, integration health checks |\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## 4. WORKFLOW STEPS\n325: \n326: ### Step 1: Load deep-agent-improvement Skill\n327: \n328: ```\n329: Read(\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md\")\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ### Step 2: Run Integration Scan\n333: \n334: ```bash\n335: node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs --agent={agent_name} --output={spec_folder}/improvement/integration-report.json\n336: ```\n337: \n338: Review the integration report: mirror sync status, command coverage, skill references.\n339: \n340: ### Step 3: Generate Profile\n341: \n342: ```bash\n343: node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/generate-profile.cjs --agent={target_path} --output={spec_folder}/improvement/dynamic-profile.json\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Step 4: Initialize Runtime\n347: \n348: Create the improvement directory structure and copy templates:\n349: ```bash\n350: mkdir -p {spec_folder}/improvement/candidates {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs\n351: ```\n352: Copy config, strategy, charter, and manifest from skill assets into runtime root.\n353: \n354: ### Step 5: Execute Loop\n355: \n356: Load the matching YAML workflow based on execution mode:\n357: - **AUTONOMOUS** -> `assets/deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_auto.yaml`\n358: - **INTERACTIVE** -> `assets/deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_confirm.yaml`\n359: \n360: Execute the YAML workflow step by step. Each iteration:\n361: 1. Scan integration surfaces (refresh)\n362: 2. Dispatch `@deep-agent-improvement` to write one bounded candidate\n363: 3. Score candidate with the dynamic 5-dimension profile\n364: 4. Run benchmark fixtures\n365: 5. Append results to JSONL ledger\n366: 6. Reduce state, refresh dashboard\n367: 7. Check stop conditions (converged via legal-stop bundle, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, manualStop, error, stuckRecovery)\n368: \n369: ### Step 6: Review Results\n370: \n371: After loop exits, present:\n372: - `{spec_folder}/improvement/agent-improvement-dashboard.md` — dimensional progress + stop status\n373: - `{spec_folder}/improvement/experiment-registry.json` — per-profile metrics + best-known state\n374: - Recommendation: continue, promote (if eligible), or stop\n375: \n376: ### Step 6B: Journal Emission\n377: \n378: At each journal boundary, the orchestrator MUST emit events via `improvement-journal.cjs`. The CLI entrypoint accepts `--emit`, `--journal`, and `--details`:\n379: \n380: ```bash\n381: # At session start:\n382: node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/improvement-journal.cjs --emit session_start --journal specs/042/008/improvement/improvement-journal.jsonl --details '{\"sessionId\":\"imp-2026-04-11T12-00-00Z\",\"target\":\"deep-research\",\"charter\":\"...\",\"startedAt\":\"2026-04-11T12:00:00Z\"}'\n383: \n384: # At iteration boundaries:\n385: # candidate_generated after the candidate is written\n386: # candidate_scored after scoring completes\n387: # gate_evaluation after stop-check or operator-gate evaluation\n388: # The CLI form carries boundary metadata inside details because the helper's CLI does not expose top-level iteration/candidate fields.\n389: \n390: # At session end:\n391: # node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/improvement-journal.cjs --emit session_end --journal {spec_folder}/improvement/improvement-journal.jsonl --details '{\"stopReason\":\"blockedStop\",\"sessionOutcome\":\"advisoryOnly\",\"endedAt\":\"2026-04-11T12:05:00Z\",\"totalIterations\":3}'\n392: ```\n393: \n394: ### Step 6C: Stop-Reason Reporting\n395: \n396: After loop exits, classify the termination:\n397: \n398: **stopReason** (WHY):\n399: - `converged` — All legal-stop gate bundles passed\n400: - `maxIterationsReached` — Hit `max_iterations` limit\n401: - `blockedStop` — Convergence math triggered but gate bundles failed\n402: - `manualStop` — User cancelled\n403: - `error` — Script or infra failure\n404: - `stuckRecovery` — Stuck detection triggered and recovery exhausted\n405: \n406: **sessionOutcome** (WHAT):\n407: - `keptBaseline` — Baseline retained\n408: - `promoted` — Candidate promoted to canonical target\n409: - `rolledBack` — Promotion reversed\n410: - `advisoryOnly` — Assessment only, no mutation\n411: \n412: ### Step 6D: Session Boundary (current release)\n413: \n414: `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` is one-session-only in the current release. Every invocation starts a fresh `new`-mode session with generation 1, writes a new journal, and evaluates candidates from iteration 1 for that session.\n415: \n416: Do **not** document or attempt journal replay, iteration carry-forward, or `resume`/`restart`/`fork`/`completed-continue` behavior here. Those lineage modes were described in earlier drafts but have no shipped runtime wiring; see `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md §Resume/Continuation Semantics (current release)` for the canonical retraction.\n417: \n418: ### Step 7: Return Status\n419: \n420: - Completed normally: `STATUS=OK ITERATIONS={N} BEST_SCORE={score}`\n421: - User cancelled: `STATUS=CANCELLED`\n422: - Max iterations: `STATUS=OK REASON=\"max_iterations_reached\"`\n423: - Converged: `STATUS=OK REASON=\"converged\"` (when all 5 legal-stop gates pass)\n424: - Error: `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"{message}\"`\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ## 5. EXAMPLES\n429: \n430: ### Evaluate Handover Agent (Interactive)\n431: \n432: ```\n433: /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop \".opencode/agents/debug.md\" :confirm --spec-folder=specs/041/008\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ### Evaluate Any Agent (Dynamic Profile, Autonomous)\n437: \n438: ```\n439: /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop \".opencode/agents/debug.md\" :auto --iterations=3\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### Quick Integration Health Check\n443: \n444: ```\n445: /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop \".opencode/agents/review.md\" :auto --iterations=1\n446: ```\n447: \n448: ### Prompt for Target Selection\n449: \n450: ```\n451: /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop :confirm\n452: ```\n453: Setup phase lists available agents and asks for selection.\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ## 6. EXAMPLE OUTPUT\n458: \n459: ```\n460: Agent Improvement Loop Complete\n461: ────────────────────────────────\n462: \n463: Target: .opencode/agents/debug.md\n464: Profile: generated dynamic profile\n465: Scoring: 5-dimension dynamic\n466: Iterations: 3\n467: \n468: Dimensional Scores (final):\n469:   Structural:    100 (best: 100, trend: ->)\n470:   Rule Coherence: 95 (best: 95, trend: ->)\n471:   Integration:   100 (best: 100, trend: ->)\n472:   Output Quality:  90 (best: 95, trend: down)\n473:   System Fitness: 100 (best: 100, trend: ->)\n474: \n475: Weighted Score: 97/100\n476: Stop Reason: converged (all 5 legal-stop gates passed) after 3 iterations\n477: \n478: Artifacts:\n479:   Dashboard: specs/041/008/improvement/agent-improvement-dashboard.md\n480:   Registry:  specs/041/008/improvement/experiment-registry.json\n481:   Candidates: 3 written to specs/041/008/improvement/candidates/\n482: \n483: STATUS=OK ITERATIONS=3 BEST_SCORE=97 REASON=\"converged\"\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## 7. NOTES\n489: \n490: - **Skill dependency**: Requires `deep-agent-improvement` at `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/`\n491: - **Promotion**: Promotion remains guarded by evidence, repeatability, and operator approval.\n492: - **Scoring**: All 5 dimensions are deterministic (regex, string matching, file existence). No LLM-as-judge.\n493: - **Stop rules**: Loop stops on `converged` (legal-stop bundle pass + stable trajectory), max iterations, or infra failure threshold.\n494: - **Runtime parity**: Agent exists across 4 runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .gemini, .codex). Scanner checks all (`.gemini/agents/` path corrected in 060/002).\n495: - **Benchmark assets** (post-060/005): static at `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json` + `assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-fixtures/*.json`. Materializer at `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` writes fixture markdown to `{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/` before `run-benchmark.cjs` consumes them. `benchmark_completed` event is gated on `report.json` existing.\n496: - **Legal-stop emission** (post-060/005): YAML emits nested `legal_stop_evaluated.details.gateResults.{contractGate,behaviorGate,integrationGate,evidenceGate,improvementGate}` matching the reducer consumer shape. Flat `gateResult/gateName` is retired.\n497: - **Stop-reason enum** (post-060/005): canonical values are `converged | maxIterationsReached | blockedStop | manualStop | error | stuckRecovery`. Old `plateau`/`benchmarkPlateau` retired.\n498: - **CRITIC PASS verbatim emission** (post-060/006): `@deep-agent-improvement` body now mandates the 6 challenge labels appear verbatim in candidate JSON `critic_pass` field. Reviewers and stress tests grep for the exact strings.\n499: \n500: ---\n501: \n502: ## 8. MODEL-BENCHMARK MODE (LANE B)\n503: \n504: This command is the **Lane A** (agent-improvement) entry point. The underlying `deep-agent-improvement` skill ALSO supports a separate **model-benchmark** mode (Lane B) that benchmarks a model or prompt framework instead of mutating an agent file. It shares the candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams with the agent-improvement path.\n505: \n506: **Lane B now has its own command: `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`.** When this command resolves `lane=model-benchmark` (via `--lane=model-benchmark`, a `--profile` / benchmark-profile arg, or the Q(lane) answer), it auto-routes to that dedicated command and loads `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_{auto,confirm}.yaml` instead of the agent-improvement YAMLs. When an agent path is supplied (the normal Lane A invocation) the lane resolves to `agent-improvement` automatically and this command runs exactly as before.\n507: \n508: - **Entry point**: `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs` resolves `--mode`. Default or `--mode=agent-improvement` routes to `scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs` (this command's path, unchanged). `--mode=model-benchmark` runs `scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` then `scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs`. An unknown mode warns to stderr and falls back to agent-improvement.\n509: - **Dispatcher**: `scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` is the model-agnostic dispatcher (executor routing across cli-opencode, cli-claude-code, cli-codex, cli-gemini, cli-devin). It loads only on the model-benchmark path, never in agent-improvement mode.\n510: - **Scorer selection**: `run-benchmark.cjs --scorer pattern` (default) uses the byte-identical heading/pattern matcher. `--scorer 5dim` routes materialized outputs through `scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs` (the ported 120/003 five-dimension scorer: deterministic checks plus a pluggable grader). `--grader noop` (default) stays deterministic with no model dispatch; `--grader mock` or `--grader llm` select the stub or real grader.\n511: - **Records**: every state record carries `mode: agent-improvement` or `mode: model-benchmark`. Benchmark reports and `benchmark_run` records carry `scoringMethod: pattern|5dim` for downstream attribution.\n512: - **Hardening env gates**: `DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0` refuses criteria-driven shell execution in the 5-dim scorer, and `DEEP_AGENT_GRADER_CACHE_RAW=0` redacts raw grader output from the on-disk cache. Both default permissive for backward compatibility.\n513: \n514: Canonical source of truth: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` §4 LANE B: MODEL-BENCHMARK. Provenance: built in spec 121/003, remediated in 121/004, opt-in scorer and docs in 121/005.\n515: \n516: ---\n517: \n518: ## 9. RELATED COMMANDS\n519: \n520: | Command | Purpose |\n521: | --- | --- |\n522: | `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` | Lane B: benchmark a model or prompt framework (auto-routed from here when `--lane=model-benchmark`) |\n523: | `/speckit:complete` | Full spec-driven development workflow |\n524: | `/prompt` | Improve AI prompts with DEPTH + CLEAR scoring |\n525: | `/deep:start-review-loop` | Iterative code review with convergence detection |\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## 10. VIOLATION SELF-DETECTION (BLOCKING)\n530: \n531: **YOU ARE IN VIOLATION IF YOU:**\n532: \n533: **Phase Violations:**\n534: - Executed workflow without @general agent verification\n535: - Started executing steps before all Setup Phase fields are set\n536: - Asked questions in MULTIPLE separate prompts instead of ONE consolidated prompt\n537: - Inferred target agent from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n538: - Auto-selected spec folder without user confirmation\n539: \n540: **Workflow Violations (Steps 1-7):**\n541: - Skipped integration scan before candidate generation\n542: - Loaded wrong YAML workflow for execution mode\n543: - Dispatched agents from this markdown command body (YAML owns loop execution)\n544: - Claimed a target-specific promotion carve-out that is not part of the current release contract\n545: - Modified canonical agent file directly instead of writing packet-local candidate\n546: \n547: **VIOLATION RECOVERY PROTOCOL:**\n548: ```\n549: FOR PHASE VIOLATIONS:\n550: 1. STOP immediately\n551: 2. STATE: \"I [specific violation]. Correcting now.\"\n552: 3. PRESENT the single consolidated prompt with ALL applicable questions\n553: 4. WAIT for user response\n554: 5. RESUME only after all fields are set\n555: \n556: FOR WORKFLOW VIOLATIONS:\n557: 1. STOP immediately\n558: 2. STATE: \"I skipped STEP [X] by [specific action]. Correcting now.\"\n559: 3. RETURN to the skipped step\n560: 4. COMPLETE all activities for that step\n561: 5. CONTINUE to next step in sequence\n562: ```\n563: \n564: **If ANY violation:** STOP -> State violation -> Return to correct step -> Complete properly\n\n(End of file - total 564 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: \"Evaluate and improve any agent: 5 dimensions, proposals, scoring, guarded promotion. :auto/:confirm.\"\nargument-hint: \"<agent_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--iterations=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\n---\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n> 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\n> 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\n>\n> This command is **general-agent based** — orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill invocation.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md","time":{"start":1780130238568,"end":1780130238579}},"id":"prt_e7807cef7001XRKAZrE6MTONkI","sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","messageID":"msg_e7807b201001CLinaHE7kb9M37"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780130239105,"sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_wcs4rg00JjvSUyx9TuZa1219","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: \"Benchmark a model or prompt framework: fixtures, pattern or 5dim scoring, deterministic or graded runs. :auto/:confirm.\"\n3: argument-hint: \"<profile_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--scorer=pattern|5dim] [--grader=noop|mock|llm] [--iterations=N] [--executor=NAME --model=NAME] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\n5: ---\n6: \n7: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL - READ FIRST**\n8: >\n9: > This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n10: >\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n12: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n13: > 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\n14: > 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n15: > 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\n16: >\n17: > This command is **general-agent based** - orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill invocation in model-benchmark mode.\n18: > This command is the dedicated Lane B entry. It sets `lane = model-benchmark` directly. It does NOT ask a lane question.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: # 🚨 PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n23: \n24: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n25: \n26: ```\n27: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n28: \n29: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n30: │\n31: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n32: │   ├─ You can orchestrate deep-agent-improvement invocation\n33: │   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n34: │   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n35: │\n36: ├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n37: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to Setup Phase\n38: │\n39: └─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n40:     │\n41:     ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n42:     │\n43:     ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n44:     │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n45:     │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n46:     │   │                                                            │\n47:     │   │ This command orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill     │\n48:     │   │ invocation in model-benchmark mode and runs general-agent based. │\n49:     │   │                                                            │\n50:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n51:     │   │   /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop [arguments]             │\n52:     │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53:     │\n54:     └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Phase Output:**\n58: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: # 🔒 UNIFIED SETUP PHASE\n63: \n64: **FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n65: \n66: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n67: \n68: This command fixes `lane = model-benchmark`. There is no lane question. The lane is implied by the command name.\n69: \n70: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n71: \n72: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n73: \n74: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n75: \n76: 1. **Tier 1 - Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist a config record under `{spec_folder}/improvement/model-benchmark-config.json` (shape: `lane: \"model-benchmark\"`, `profilePath`, `specFolder`, `outputsDir`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `scoringMethod`, `grader`, optional `executor`, optional `model`, and when `grader = llm` also thread `executor`/`model` into `modelBenchmarkConfig.target_model` so `dispatch-model.cjs` reads them), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n77: \n78: 2. **Tier 2 - Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. `profile_path` absence is not ambiguity because it has a default, and `executor`/`model` are only required when `grader = llm`.\n79: \n80: 3. **Tier 3 - Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n81: \n82: `:confirm` path stays unchanged - see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n83: \n84: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n85: \n86: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n87: \n88: ```yaml\n89: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n90:   profile_path: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json  # optional; default profile when omitted\n91:   spec_folder: specs/121/008  # required spec folder path or explicit runtime folder\n92:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n93:   scoring_method: pattern  # pattern (default) or 5dim\n94:   grader: noop  # noop (default) | mock | llm\n95:   max_iterations: 5  # positive integer; default 5\n96:   executor: cli-codex  # required only when grader = llm; one of cli-opencode | cli-claude-code | cli-codex | cli-gemini | cli-devin\n97:   model: gpt-5.5  # required only when grader = llm; model id for the chosen executor\n98: ```\n99: \n100: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default, marker fields take precedence over $ARGUMENTS flags, unknown fields warn, malformed lines parse-error). When `grader != llm`, any `executor`/`model` marker fields are ignored with a warning.\n101: \n102: ### Default Resolution Table\n103: \n104: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n105: |-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|\n106: | `lane` | Y | fixed by command | `model-benchmark` | N |\n107: | `profile_path` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` profile path, or marker `profile_path` | `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json` | N |\n108: | `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, or requires-ask | none | Y |\n109: | `outputs_dir` | Y | derived from `spec_folder` | `{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs` | N |\n110: | `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |\n111: | `scoring_method` | Y | flag `--scorer`, marker `scoring_method`, Q3 equivalent, or default | `pattern` | N |\n112: | `grader` | Y | flag `--grader`, marker `grader`, Q4 equivalent, or default | `noop` | N |\n113: | `max_iterations` | Y | flag `--iterations`, marker `max_iterations`, or default | `5` | N |\n114: | `executor` | Conditional | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, required only when `grader = llm` | none | N |\n115: | `model` | Conditional | flag `--model`, marker `model`, required only when `grader = llm` | none | N |\n116: \n117: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n118: \n119: **🚨 SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION**\n120: \n121: This workflow uses a SINGLE consolidated prompt to gather ALL required inputs in ONE user interaction.\n122: \n123: **Round-trip optimization:** This workflow requires only 1 user interaction for setup.\n124: \n125: ```\n126: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n127: \n128: 1. SET lane = \"model-benchmark\" (fixed by this command, never asked).\n129: \n130: 2. CHECK for mode suffix in $ARGUMENTS or command invocation:\n131:    ├─ \":auto\" suffix detected → execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\" (pre-set, omit Q2)\n132:    ├─ \":confirm\" suffix detected → execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\" (pre-set, omit Q2)\n133:    └─ No suffix → execution_mode = \"ASK\" (include Q2 in prompt)\n134: \n135: 3. CHECK if $ARGUMENTS contains a profile path:\n136:    ├─ IF present (a *.json benchmark profile) → profile_path = detected value, omit Q0\n137:    └─ IF missing → Q0 offered with the default profile pre-selected\n138: \n139: 4. CHECK for --spec-folder flag:\n140:    ├─ IF present → spec_folder = value, omit Q1\n141:    └─ IF missing → include Q1 in prompt\n142: \n143: 5. CHECK for --scorer / --grader / --iterations flags:\n144:    ├─ IF --scorer present → scoring_method = value, omit Q3\n145:    ├─ IF --grader present → grader = value, omit Q4\n146:    ├─ IF --iterations present → max_iterations = value\n147:    └─ IF missing → scoring_method = pattern (default), grader = noop (default), max_iterations = 5 (default)\n148: \n149: 6. List available benchmark profiles for Q0:\n150:    $ ls .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/*.json\n151: \n152: 7. List recent spec folders for Q1:\n153:    $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n154: \n155: 8. ASK user with SINGLE consolidated prompt (include only applicable questions):\n156: \n157:    ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n158:    │ **Before proceeding, please answer:**                          │\n159:    │                                                                │\n160:    │ **Q0. Benchmark Profile** (if not provided in command):         │\n161:    │    Which benchmark profile should drive the fixtures?            │\n162:    │    A) Default - assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json │\n163:    │    B) Other - paste a profile path                              │\n164:    │                                                                │\n165:    │ **Q1. Spec Folder** (if no --spec-folder flag):                 │\n166:    │    A) Use existing spec folder: [list if found]                │\n167:    │    B) Create new spec folder                                   │\n168:    │    C) Use temporary directory                                  │\n169:    │                                                                │\n170:    │ **Q2. Execution Mode** (if no :auto/:confirm suffix):            │\n171:    │    A) Autonomous - run loop without approval gates             │\n172:    │    B) Interactive - confirm at each iteration                   │\n173:    │                                                                │\n174:    │ **Q3. Scoring Method**:                                        │\n175:    │    A) Pattern - heading/pattern matcher (default, fastest)     │\n176:    │    B) 5dim - ported 5-dimension scorer (deterministic + grader)│\n177:    │                                                                │\n178:    │ **Q4. Grader**:                                                │\n179:    │    A) noop - deterministic, no model dispatch (default)        │\n180:    │    B) mock - stub grader                                       │\n181:    │    C) llm - real model dispatch (requires Q5)                  │\n182:    │                                                                │\n183:    │ **Q5. Executor + Model** (ONLY if Q4 = llm):                   │\n184:    │    Which executor and model? e.g. \"cli-codex, gpt-5.5\"         │\n185:    │    Executors: cli-opencode | cli-claude-code | cli-codex |     │\n186:    │               cli-gemini | cli-devin                           │\n187:    │                                                                │\n188:    │ Reply format: \"A, A, A, A, A\" or                               │\n189:    │ \"default, B, B, B, C, cli-codex gpt-5.5\"                       │\n190:    └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n191: \n192: 9. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n193: \n194: 10. Parse response and store ALL results:\n195:    - lane = \"model-benchmark\" (fixed)\n196:    - profile_path = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS or default profile]\n197:    - spec_folder = [from Q1 or --spec-folder]\n198:    - outputs_dir = [{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs]\n199:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE from suffix or Q2]\n200:    - scoring_method = [pattern or 5dim from Q3 or --scorer]\n201:    - grader = [noop/mock/llm from Q4 or --grader]\n202:    - max_iterations = [from --iterations or default 5]\n203:    - executor = [from Q5, only when grader = llm]\n204:    - model = [from Q5, only when grader = llm]\n205: \n206: 11. SET STATUS: ✅ PASSED\n207: \n208: **STOP HERE** - Wait for user to answer ALL applicable questions before continuing.\n209: \n210: ⛔ HARD STOP: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n211: ⛔ NEVER ask a lane question - this command IS the model-benchmark entry\n212: ⛔ NEVER infer the profile from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n213: ⛔ NEVER auto-select spec folder without user confirmation\n214: ⛔ NEVER request executor/model when grader is not llm\n215: ⛔ NEVER split these questions into multiple prompts\n216: ⛔ NEVER assume what the user wants based on open files or recent activity\n217: ```\n218: \n219: **Phase Output:**\n220: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n221: - `lane = model-benchmark`\n222: - `profile_path = ________________`\n223: - `spec_folder = ________________`\n224: - `outputs_dir = ________________`\n225: - `execution_mode = ________________`\n226: - `scoring_method = ________________`\n227: - `grader = ________________`\n228: - `max_iterations = ________________`\n229: - `executor = ________________` (only when grader = llm)\n230: - `model = ________________` (only when grader = llm)\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## PHASE STATUS VERIFICATION (BLOCKING)\n235: \n236: **Before continuing to the workflow, verify ALL values are set:**\n237: \n238: | FIELD                  | REQUIRED      | YOUR VALUE | SOURCE                  |\n239: | ---------------------- | ------------- | ---------- | ----------------------- |\n240: | general_agent_verified | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Automatic check         |\n241: | lane                   | ✅ Yes         | model-benchmark | Fixed by command   |\n242: | profile_path           | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q0, $ARGUMENTS, or default |\n243: | spec_folder            | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q1 or --spec-folder     |\n244: | outputs_dir            | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Derived from spec_folder |\n245: | execution_mode         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Suffix or Q2            |\n246: | scoring_method         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q3 or --scorer          |\n247: | grader                 | ✅ Yes         | ______     | Q4 or --grader          |\n248: | max_iterations         | ✅ Yes         | ______     | --iterations or 5       |\n249: | executor               | Conditional   | ______     | Q5 (only when grader=llm) |\n250: | model                  | Conditional   | ______     | Q5 (only when grader=llm) |\n251: \n252: ```\n253: VERIFICATION CHECK:\n254: ├─ ALL required fields have values?\n255: │   ├─ grader == llm AND (executor missing OR model missing)?\n256: │   │   └─ Re-prompt Q5 only\n257: │   ├─ YES → Proceed to \"INSTRUCTIONS\" section below\n258: │   └─ NO  → Re-prompt for missing values only\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## CONSTRAINTS\n264: \n265: - **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n266: - **DO NOT** ask a lane question - this command fixes `lane = model-benchmark`\n267: - **DO NOT** infer the benchmark profile from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n268: - **DO NOT** request executor/model unless `grader = llm`\n269: - **DO NOT** start the loop without all setup values resolved\n270: - **FIRST ACTION** is always: run Phase 0, run Setup, then load YAML workflow\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: # Benchmark Model or Prompt Framework\n275: \n276: Benchmark a model or prompt framework against a fixture profile. The skill materializes benchmark fixtures into packet-local outputs, scores them with the pattern matcher or the ported 5-dimension scorer, records mode-aware state, and never mutates a canonical agent file.\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## 1. PURPOSE\n281: \n282: Run a bounded model-benchmark loop that:\n283: 1. Resolves the benchmark profile (default profile or an explicit profile path)\n284: 2. Materializes the profile's fixtures into packet-local markdown outputs\n285: 3. Runs the fixtures against those outputs with the selected scorer (`pattern` or `5dim`)\n286: 4. Selects a grader for the 5-dimension path (`noop` deterministic, `mock` stub, or `llm` real dispatch)\n287: 5. Records mode-aware state where every record carries `mode: model-benchmark` and every benchmark report carries `scoringMethod: pattern|5dim`\n288: 6. Reduces evidence into a benchmark report and presents the result\n289: 7. Stops on max iterations, convergence, or infra failure\n290: \n291: This command drives the model-benchmark lane only. To improve an agent definition, use `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` (the agent-improvement lane).\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## 2. CONTRACT\n296: \n297: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` - optional profile path, optional mode suffix, optional spec folder, optional scorer/grader flags, optional executor+model (only with `--grader=llm`)\n298: **Outputs:** benchmark packet state under `{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/` + `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n299: \n300: ### Lane B Runtime Contract\n301: \n302: The model-benchmark loop runs through `loop-host.cjs` in model-benchmark mode:\n303: \n304: ```bash\n305: node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n306:   --mode=model-benchmark \\\n307:   --profile {profile_path} \\\n308:   --outputs-dir {outputs_dir} \\\n309:   --scorer {scoring_method} \\\n310:   --grader {grader}\n311: ```\n312: \n313: - `loop-host.cjs` resolves `--mode=model-benchmark`, then runs `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` and `run-benchmark.cjs` in that order (the EC-5 ordering: materialize MUST run and succeed before run-benchmark, or scoring has no inputs).\n314: - `--profile` and `--outputs-dir` are required for the model-benchmark path. `loop-host.cjs` forwards `--output`, `--state-log`, `--label`, and `--profiles-dir` through to `run-benchmark.cjs`.\n315: - `--scorer pattern` (default, heading/pattern matcher) or `--scorer 5dim` (ported 5-dimension scorer via `scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`). `--scorer` and `--grader` are consumed at the `run-benchmark.cjs` layer.\n316: - `--grader noop` (default, deterministic, no model dispatch) or `--grader mock` (stub) or `--grader llm` (real model dispatch).\n317: - **Threading executor/model when `grader = llm`:** the gathered `executor` and `model` values are NOT loop-host flags. Setup MUST persist them into `modelBenchmarkConfig.target_model` (executor + model) inside the runtime config that `dispatch-model.cjs` reads, so the dispatcher resolves the requested executor and model. Setup persists `executor` and `model` into the Lane B config record (see Step 3) and the config record threads `modelBenchmarkConfig.target_model`. Without that thread, `dispatch-model.cjs` falls back to its built-in defaults and the gathered values are silently dropped.\n318: - An unknown `--mode` warns to stderr and falls back to agent-improvement. An unknown `--scorer` warns and falls back to `pattern`.\n319: \n320: ### Default Profile and Fixtures\n321: \n322: - Default profile: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json`\n323: - Fixtures: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-fixtures/` (`fixture-baseline`, `fixture-improved`, `fixture-edge`)\n324: \n325: ### User Input\n326: \n327: ```text\n328: $ARGUMENTS\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## 3. SCORING AND GRADER REFERENCE\n334: \n335: ### Scorers\n336: \n337: | Scorer | Flag | What It Does | Use When |\n338: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n339: | Pattern | `--scorer pattern` | Byte-identical heading/pattern matcher (default) | Fast deterministic structural benchmarking |\n340: | 5dim | `--scorer 5dim` | Ported 5-dimension scorer (`scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`) with deterministic checks plus a pluggable grader | Richer multi-dimension evaluation of produced outputs |\n341: \n342: ### Graders (5-dimension path)\n343: \n344: | Grader | Flag | Behavior |\n345: | --- | --- | --- |\n346: | noop | `--grader noop` | Deterministic, no model dispatch (default) |\n347: | mock | `--grader mock` | Stub grader for wiring and tests |\n348: | llm | `--grader llm` | Real model dispatch via `dispatch-model.cjs`, requires an executor + model |\n349: \n350: ### Executor Routing (only on `--grader llm`)\n351: \n352: `dispatch-model.cjs` is the executor router. It is loaded only on the model-benchmark path and only when `grader = llm`. Supported executors: `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, `cli-codex`, `cli-gemini`, `cli-devin`.\n353: \n354: ### Hardening Env Gates\n355: \n356: - `DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0` refuses criteria-driven shell execution in the 5-dim scorer.\n357: - `DEEP_AGENT_GRADER_CACHE_RAW=0` redacts raw grader output from the on-disk cache.\n358: - Both default to the permissive value for backward compatibility.\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## 4. WORKFLOW STEPS\n363: \n364: ### Step 1: Load deep-agent-improvement Skill\n365: \n366: ```\n367: Read(\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md\")\n368: ```\n369: \n370: Focus on §4 LANE B: MODEL-BENCHMARK for the canonical contract.\n371: \n372: ### Step 2: Resolve Profile\n373: \n374: Confirm `profile_path` exists. When the user did not supply one, use the default profile:\n375: ```bash\n376: ls .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### Step 3: Initialize Runtime\n380: \n381: Create the benchmark output directory:\n382: ```bash\n383: mkdir -p {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs\n384: ```\n385: Persist the config record to `{spec_folder}/improvement/model-benchmark-config.json` (`lane`, `profilePath`, `specFolder`, `outputsDir`, `executionMode`, `scoringMethod`, `grader`, optional `executor`, optional `model`). When `grader = llm`, also thread the gathered `executor` and `model` into `modelBenchmarkConfig.target_model` (shape: `{ \"modelBenchmarkConfig\": { \"target_model\": { \"executor\": \"<executor>\", \"model\": \"<model>\" } } }`) so `dispatch-model.cjs` resolves the requested executor and model instead of its built-in defaults.\n386: \n387: ### Step 4: Execute Loop\n388: \n389: Load the matching YAML workflow based on execution mode:\n390: - **AUTONOMOUS** -> `assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml`\n391: - **INTERACTIVE** -> `assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_confirm.yaml`\n392: \n393: Execute the YAML workflow step by step. Each iteration:\n394: 1. Materialize benchmark fixtures into packet-local markdown outputs (`materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`)\n395: 2. Run the fixtures with the selected scorer and grader (`run-benchmark.cjs`)\n396: 3. Record mode-aware state where each record carries `mode: model-benchmark` and the report carries `scoringMethod: pattern|5dim`\n397: 4. Reduce state and refresh the benchmark report\n398: 5. Check stop conditions (converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, manualStop, error, stuckRecovery)\n399: \n400: The orchestrator never runs `materialize` and `run-benchmark` out of order. `loop-host.cjs` enforces materialize-before-benchmark (EC-5).\n401: \n402: ### Step 5: Review Results\n403: \n404: After the loop exits, present:\n405: - `{spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/report.json` - fixture scores, aggregate, `scoringMethod`\n406: - Per-fixture pass/fail against the profile thresholds (`requiredAggregateScore`, `minimumFixtureScore`)\n407: - Recommendation: continue, promote (if eligible), or stop\n408: \n409: ### Step 6: Promotion (benchmark-report based, optional)\n410: \n411: Lane B promotes from the benchmark report, not from an agent-scored candidate file. When evidence and approval allow it:\n412: ```bash\n413: node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/promote-candidate.cjs --benchmark-report {spec_folder}/improvement/benchmark-outputs/report.json ...\n414: ```\n415: When `--benchmark-report` is supplied, `promote-candidate.cjs` runs its benchmark-mode promotion path. It promotes on the report basis when the report carries `status: benchmark-complete` with a `benchmark-pass` recommendation, bypassing the agent-scored-file requirement that the agent-improvement path uses. Promotion stays guarded by the benchmark aggregate gate, repeatability, and operator approval, and it refuses to act while the runtime config is still proposal-only.\n416: \n417: ### Step 7: Return Status\n418: \n419: - Completed normally: `STATUS=OK SCORING={scoring_method} GRADER={grader} AGGREGATE={score}`\n420: - User cancelled: `STATUS=CANCELLED`\n421: - Max iterations: `STATUS=OK REASON=\"max_iterations_reached\"`\n422: - Converged: `STATUS=OK REASON=\"converged\"`\n423: - Error: `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"{message}\"`\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## 5. EXAMPLES\n428: \n429: ### Default Profile, Pattern Scorer (Autonomous)\n430: \n431: ```\n432: /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop :auto --spec-folder=specs/121/008\n433: ```\n434: Uses the default profile, `--scorer pattern`, `--grader noop`.\n435: \n436: ### Explicit Profile, 5-Dimension Scorer (Interactive)\n437: \n438: ```\n439: /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop \".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json\" :confirm --scorer=5dim\n440: ```\n441: Setup asks the remaining questions. Grader stays `noop` unless changed.\n442: \n443: ### 5-Dimension Scorer with Real Model Dispatch\n444: \n445: ```\n446: /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop :auto --spec-folder=specs/121/008 --scorer=5dim --grader=llm --executor=cli-codex --model=gpt-5.5\n447: ```\n448: Routes graded scoring through `dispatch-model.cjs` to the named executor and model.\n449: \n450: ### Prompt for Setup\n451: \n452: ```\n453: /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop :confirm\n454: ```\n455: Setup phase lists available profiles, defaults the profile to `default.json`, and asks for spec folder, scorer, and grader.\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: ## 6. EXAMPLE OUTPUT\n460: \n461: ```\n462: Model Benchmark Loop Complete\n463: ─────────────────────────────\n464: \n465: Profile: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json\n466: Scoring: pattern\n467: Grader:  noop\n468: Mode:    model-benchmark\n469: \n470: Fixture Scores:\n471:   fixture-baseline: 82 (pass)\n472:   fixture-improved: 91 (pass)\n473:   fixture-edge:     74 (pass, >= minimumFixtureScore 70)\n474: \n475: Aggregate Score: 82 (>= requiredAggregateScore 80)\n476: scoringMethod: pattern\n477: Stop Reason: converged\n478: \n479: Artifacts:\n480:   Report: specs/121/008/improvement/benchmark-outputs/report.json\n481:   Outputs: specs/121/008/improvement/benchmark-outputs/\n482: \n483: STATUS=OK SCORING=pattern GRADER=noop AGGREGATE=82 REASON=\"converged\"\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## 7. NOTES\n489: \n490: - **Skill dependency**: Requires `deep-agent-improvement` at `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/`\n491: - **Lane**: This command fixes `lane = model-benchmark`. It never mutates a canonical agent file. Use `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` for the agent-improvement lane.\n492: - **Entry point**: `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark` runs `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` then `run-benchmark.cjs` in that order. Required flags: `--profile`, `--outputs-dir`.\n493: - **Scorer default**: `--scorer pattern` keeps the byte-identical heading/pattern matcher. `--scorer 5dim` is opt-in and lazily loads `scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`.\n494: - **Grader default**: `--grader noop` stays deterministic with no model dispatch. `--grader llm` is the only grader that loads `dispatch-model.cjs`.\n495: - **Mode-aware records**: every state record carries `mode: model-benchmark` and benchmark reports carry `scoringMethod: pattern|5dim` for downstream attribution.\n496: - **Promotion**: Lane B promotes via `promote-candidate.cjs --benchmark-report`, which runs a benchmark-mode promotion path that gates on a `benchmark-complete` report with a `benchmark-pass` recommendation instead of an agent-scored candidate file. It stays guarded by the benchmark aggregate gate, repeatability, and operator approval.\n497: - **Provenance**: model-benchmark mode built in spec 121/003, remediated in 121/004, opt-in scorer and docs in 121/005, command entry in 121/008. Canonical source of truth: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` §4 LANE B: MODEL-BENCHMARK.\n498: \n499: ---\n500: \n501: ## 8. RELATED COMMANDS\n502: \n503: | Command | Purpose |\n504: | --- | --- |\n505: | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` | Improve an agent definition (agent-improvement lane) |\n506: | `/speckit:complete` | Full spec-driven development workflow |\n507: | `/prompt` | Improve AI prompts with DEPTH + CLEAR scoring |\n508: | `/deep:start-review-loop` | Iterative code review with convergence detection |\n509: \n510: ---\n511: \n512: ## 9. VIOLATION SELF-DETECTION (BLOCKING)\n513: \n514: **YOU ARE IN VIOLATION IF YOU:**\n515: \n516: **Phase Violations:**\n517: - Executed workflow without @general agent verification\n518: - Started executing steps before all Setup Phase fields are set\n519: - Asked a lane question instead of fixing `lane = model-benchmark`\n520: - Asked questions in MULTIPLE separate prompts instead of ONE consolidated prompt\n521: - Inferred the benchmark profile from context, screenshots, or conversation history\n522: - Requested executor/model when `grader` is not `llm`\n523: - Auto-selected spec folder without user confirmation\n524: \n525: **Workflow Violations (Steps 1-7):**\n526: - Ran `run-benchmark.cjs` before `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` (EC-5 ordering)\n527: - Loaded wrong YAML workflow for execution mode\n528: - Loaded the agent-improvement YAML for this model-benchmark command\n529: - Dispatched agents from this markdown command body (YAML owns loop execution)\n530: - Loaded `dispatch-model.cjs` outside the `--grader llm` path\n531: - Mutated a canonical agent file (this lane never mutates agent definitions)\n532: \n533: **VIOLATION RECOVERY PROTOCOL:**\n534: ```\n535: FOR PHASE VIOLATIONS:\n536: 1. STOP immediately\n537: 2. STATE: \"I [specific violation]. Correcting now.\"\n538: 3. PRESENT the single consolidated prompt with ALL applicable questions\n539: 4. WAIT for user response\n540: 5. RESUME only after all fields are set\n541: \n542: FOR WORKFLOW VIOLATIONS:\n543: 1. STOP immediately\n544: 2. STATE: \"I skipped STEP [X] by [specific action]. Correcting now.\"\n545: 3. RETURN to the skipped step\n546: 4. COMPLETE all activities for that step\n547: 5. CONTINUE to next step in sequence\n548: ```\n549: \n550: **If ANY violation:** STOP -> State violation -> Return to correct step -> Complete properly\n\n(End of file - total 550 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: \"Benchmark a model or prompt framework: fixtures, pattern or 5dim scoring, deterministic or graded runs. :auto/:confirm.\"\nargument-hint: \"<profile_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--scorer=pattern|5dim] [--grader=noop|mock|llm] [--iterations=N] [--executor=NAME --model=NAME] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\n---\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL - READ FIRST**\n>\n> This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\n>\n> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\n> 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\n> 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\n> 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\n> 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\n>\n> This command is **general-agent based** - orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill invocation in model-benchmark mode.\n> This command is the dedicated Lane B entry. It sets `lane = model-benchmark` directly. It does NOT ask a lane question.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md","time":{"start":1780130239095,"end":1780130239104}},"id":"prt_e7807d0cf001h6XnQOiDaANL18","sessionID":"ses_187f8dff3ffekWTw11vPJPQhfy","messageID":"msg_e7807b201001CLinaHE7kb9M37"}}
